## Errors & Mistakes
- The big one: dual-copy identity issues at the IN-PROCESS seam (predicted during planning, confirmed empirically). Production crosses copies via HTTP serialization; the in-process client fixture does not. Fixed at the fixture seam, NOT by weakening client/server code.
- Cache namespace bug: CachingMiddlewareTraceServer namespaces keys by func.__name__; my wrapper's closure was named 'call' -> ALL methods cached under one namespace -> obj_delete invalidation prefixes never matched -> stale reads (test_object_deletion). Fix: call.__name__ = name. If you write another server-wrapping proxy, set __name__.
- Exceptions: e.args reconstruction broke on kwargs-style __init__ (ObjectDeletedError(message, deleted_at)) -> switched to __new__ + __dict__ transplant.
- Streaming: errors raise lazily on consumption -> translation must wrap iteration (generator), not just the call.
- Revalidation itself runs server-copy model validators -> must sit INSIDE the error-translation block (test_table_query_empty_sort_field_validation).
- rg -g '!dir/**' excludes are NOT honored by this environment's Bash rg shim -- use /usr/bin/grep --exclude-dir. Burned twice this session.

